{"title": "Regular Meeting of Council", "start_datetime": "2026-12-22 14:30:00", "end_datetime": "2026-12-22 21:30:00", "dtstamp_updated_at_datetime": "2026-07-23 07:55:22", "detail_url": "https://events.burlington.ca/meetings/Detail/2026-12-22-0930-Regular-Meeting-of-Council", "video_url": null, "agendas": [], "package": [], "meeting_type": "Council Meetings", "event_details_description": "City Council meetings are held at city hall, 426 Brant St. Requests to speak at this meeting can be made by completing the online delegation registration form at\nwww.burlington.ca/delegate\n, by submitting a written request by email to Legislative Services at\nclerks@burlington.ca\nor by phoning 905-335-7777, ext. 7481 by noon the business day before the meeting date. If you do not wish to speak, but would like to submit your comments in writing, please email your comments to\nclerks@burlington.ca\n. Correspondence (delegation notes and written comments) will be circulated to committee members.\nCouncil meetings are where the final approval takes place of items that went to the meetings of the Committee of the Whole, Pipeline to Permit Committee, Council Workshop and Audit Committee. Meeting agendas, dates or times may change. To verify information, contact the Office of the City Clerk by email at\nclerks@burlington.ca\nor at 905-335-7777 Ext. 7481. Note: Special meetings of Council may be scheduled as required.", "contact": null}
{"title": "Council Workshop Committee", "start_datetime": "2026-09-17 17:00:00", "end_datetime": "2026-09-17 20:30:00", "dtstamp_updated_at_datetime": "2026-07-23 07:55:22", "detail_url": "https://events.burlington.ca/meetings/Detail/2026-09-17-1300-Council-Workshop-Committee", "video_url": null, "agendas": [], "package": [], "meeting_type": "Council Standing Committee", "event_details_description": "Council Workshop meetings are held at city hall, 426 Brant St. Workshops are live webcasted, and archived on the city website. Council Workshop meets when time is required for training, discussions with other levels of government and outside agencies, workshops on complex matters, and strategic planning. Delegations are not permitted at Council Workshops.\nMeeting agendas, dates or times may change. To verify information, contact Legislative Services at\nclerks@burlington.ca", "contact": null}
{"title": "Council Workshop Committee", "start_datetime": "2026-11-17 14:30:00", "end_datetime": "2026-11-17 18:00:00", "dtstamp_updated_at_datetime": "2026-07-23 07:55:22", "detail_url": "https://events.burlington.ca/meetings/Detail/2026-11-17-0930-Council-Workshop-Committee", "video_url": null, "agendas": [], "package": [], "meeting_type": "Council Standing Committee", "event_details_description": "Council Workshop meetings are held at city hall, 426 Brant St. Workshops are live webcasted, and archived on the city website. Council Workshop meets when time is required for training, discussions with other levels of government and outside agencies, workshops on complex matters, and strategic planning. Delegations are not permitted at Council Workshops.\nMeeting agendas, dates or times may change. To verify information, contact Legislative Services at\nclerks@burlington.ca", "contact": null}
{"title": "Committee of Adjustment", "start_datetime": "2026-08-19 17:00:00", "end_datetime": "2026-08-20 00:00:00", "dtstamp_updated_at_datetime": "2026-07-23 07:55:22", "detail_url": "https://events.burlington.ca/meetings/Detail/2026-08-19-1300-Committee-of-Adjustment", "video_url": null, "agendas": [], "package": [], "meeting_type": "Committee of Adjustment", "event_details_description": "Committee of Adjustment\nmeetings will be held in-person at City Hall Council Chambers, 426 Brant St. and virtually via Zoom videoconferencing technology.\nRequests to delegate at a meeting can be made by submitting a written request by email to the Secretary Treasurer of the Committee of Adjustment at committeeofadjustment@burlington.ca or by phoning 905-335-7777, ext. 7629 by noon the business day before the meeting is to be held. You are encouraged to pre-register as a delegate as soon as possible to facilitate an orderly registration process.\nIt is recommended that virtual delegates include their intended remarks, which will be circulated to all members in advance, as a backup to any disruptions in technology issues that may occur.\nIf you do not wish to delegate, but would like to submit correspondence, please email your comments to committeeofadjustment@burlington.ca. Any notes and comments will be circulated to the applicant, staff and members in advance of the meeting and will forming part of the public record.\nThe link will be active 30 minutes before the start time.\nApplications will be heard in the order that they appear on the agenda or otherwise stated by the Chair.\nZoom Details\nWhen: Aug 19, 2026 1:00 PM Eastern Time (US and Canada)\nTopic:  Hybrid CoA Meeting no 15_1:00 PM\nJoin from PC, Mac, iPad, or Android:\nhttps://us06web.zoom.us/j/81284335135\nPhone one-tap:\n+16475580588,,81284335135# Canada\n+17789072071,,81284335135# Canada\nJoin via audio:\n+1 647 558 0588 Canada\n+1 778 907 2071 Canada\n+1 780 666 0144 Canada\n+1 204 272 7920 Canada\n+1 438 809 7799 Canada\n+1 587 328 1099 Canada\n+1 647 374 4685 Canada\nWebinar ID: 812 8433 5135\nInternational numbers available:\nhttps://us06web.zoom.us/u/kbfUWG58Ux", "contact": null}
{"title": "Committee of the Whole", "start_datetime": "2026-09-14 13:30:00", "end_datetime": "2026-09-14 20:30:00", "dtstamp_updated_at_datetime": "2026-07-23 07:55:22", "detail_url": "https://events.burlington.ca/meetings/Detail/2026-09-14-0930-Committee-of-the-Whole", "video_url": null, "agendas": [], "package": [], "meeting_type": "Council Standing Committee", "event_details_description": "Standing committee and City Council meetings are held at city hall, 426 Brant St. Requests to speak at this meeting can be made by completing the online delegation registration form at\nwww.burlington.ca/delegate\n, by submitting a written request by email to Legislative Services at\nclerks@burlington.ca\nor by phoning 905-335-7777, ext. 7481 by noon the Friday before the meeting date. If you do not wish to speak, but would like to submit your comments in writing, please email your comments to\nclerks@burlington.ca\n. Written correspondence will be circulated to committee members.", "contact": null}
